William Jasper DARDEN, Petitioner-Appellant, Cross-Respondent, v. Louie L. WAINWRIGHT, Secretary, Department of Corrections, State of Florida, Respondent-Appellee, Cross-Petitioner. No. 81-5590. United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Aug. 30, 1985. Robert Augustus Harper, Jr., John Perry, Tallahassee, Fla., for petitioner-appellant, cross-respondent. Richard W. Prospect, Asst. Atty. Gen., Daytona Beach, Fla., for respondent-appel-lee, cross-petitioner.

Before GODBOLD, Chief Judge, RONEY, TJOFLAT,* HILL, FAY, VANCE, KRAVITCH, JOHNSON, HENDERSON, ANDERSON and CLARK, Circuit Judges, and MORGAN, Senior Circuit Judge.**

Judge Gerald Bard Tjoflat did not participate in this decision.

Judge Joseph W. Hatchett, having recused himself, did not participate in this decision. Senior Circuit Judge Lewis R. Morgan elected to participate in this decision pursuant to 28 U.S.C. § 46(c).

*668ORDER

Darden’s motion, filed August 29, 1985, to stay the mandate for 30 days and stay his execution pending application for certio-rari, is DENIED.
